#
# Re-Bind the same prepared statement with different parameter values.
#
# Parse one statement, then Bind+Execute the unnamed portal twice with distinct
# bound values (1, then 2) before a single Sync. The unnamed portal is replaced
# on the second Bind, so this is the case that most directly depends on Bind
# carrying real parameter values — what the move to the pgpool-II pgproto build
# unblocked. PostgreSQL returns one DataRow per Execute (two total) before
# ReadyForQuery; the multigateway must relay both.
#
# Bind field layout (tab-separated):
#   'B'  portal  stmt  ncodes  nparams  [paramlen "value"]...  nresultcodes
# Each value here is one byte: "1"=1, "2"=1.
#

'P'	""	"SELECT $1::int + 100"	0
'B'	""	""	0	1	1	"1"	0
'E'	""	0
'B'	""	""	0	1	1	"2"	0
'E'	""	0
'S'
'Y'
'X'
